    <title type="text">Archimedes Project</title>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<a href="http://archimedes.fas.harvard.edu/">Archimedes
      Project</a><br /><blockquote class="tr_bq"><img
      alt="http://archimedes.fas.harvard.edu/images/archlogo-main.gif" class="decoded" height="144"
      src="http://archimedes.fas.harvard.edu/images/archlogo-main.gif" width="200" />
      </blockquote><blockquote> <span style="font-size: x-small;">This is the
      homepage of the Archimedes Project at <a href="http://www.harvard.edu/">Harvard
      University</a>. </span></blockquote><blockquote><span
      style="font-size: x-small;"> </span><span style="font-size: x-small;">The
      Archimedes Project aims to develop model interactive environments for scholarly research on the
      history of mechanics and engineering from antiquity to the Renaissance. It is designed to
      integrate research and knowledge dissemination in new ways and to serve as a proof-of-concept
      project for open digital libraries on topics in the history of science. The project is funded
      by the <a href="http://dli2.nsf.gov/">Digital Libraries Initiative Phase 2</a>
      program of the <a href="http://www.nsf.gov/">National Science Foundation</a> and is
      a joint endeavor of the <a href="http://www.fas.harvard.edu/%7Eclassics/">Department of
      the Classics</a> at Harvard University and the <a
      href="http://www.mpiwg-berlin.mpg.de/">Max Planck Institute for the History of
      Science</a> (<acronym lang="de" title="Max-Planck-Institut für
      Wissenschaftsgeschichte">MPIWG</acronym>) in Berlin, Germany. Numerous treatises on
      mechanics as well as other forms of documentation of mechanical knowledge and practices
      constitute the project corpus. Ongoing research at Harvard University and the <acronym
      lang="de" title="Max-Planck-Institut für Wissenschaftsgeschichte">MPIWG</acronym> on
      the long-term development of mechanical knowledge and its manifestation in technical
      terminology and the inferences of practitioners, engineers, and scientists plays an important
      role in the testbed design. The project demands powerful, linguistically based information
      technology for handling the variety of languages occurring in the source materials. Source
      documents are being prepared with tools such as automatic morphological analysis of Latin,
      Greek, Italian, and <a
      href="http://archimedes.fas.harvard.edu/docs/Arabic">Arabic</a>, as well as the
      automatic linking of sources to modern and historical dictionaries and reference
      works.</span></blockquote><blockquote class="tr_bq"><h3><span
      style="font-size: x-small;">Research tools on Euclid's
      <i>Elements</i></span></h3><blockquote> <span
      style="font-size: x-small;"><a
      href="http://archimedes.fas.harvard.edu/euclid/digilib.html"><b>Index of
      propositions</b></a> with links to online manuscript images.</span><br
      /> <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a
      href="http://archimedes.fas.harvard.edu/euclid/euclid_paper.pdf"><b>New technologies
      for the study of Euclid's <i>Elements</i></b></a>: paper by Mark
      Schiefsky including a description of Archimedes project technology and its application to the
      study of technical terminology and deductive structures in the
      <i>Elements</i>.</span><br /> </blockquote><h3><span
      style="font-size: x-small;">Project technology developed at
      Harvard</span></h3><ul><li><span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><a href="http://archimedes.fas.harvard.edu/arboreal/">Arboreal</a>
      (content-based <acronym title="Extensible Markup Language">XML</acronym> browser
      and annotation environment) </span></li><li><span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><a
      href="http://archimedes.fas.harvard.edu/cgi-bin/donatus">Donatus</a> (morphological
      analysis for <acronym title="Extensible Markup Language">XML</acronym> texts)
      </span><ul><li><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a
      href="http://archimedes.fas.harvard.edu/cgi-bin/morph-csv">lists of supplemental forms by
      language</a> (also available as <a
      href="http://archimedes.fas.harvard.edu/cgi-bin/morph-csv-xml"><acronym title="Extensible
      Markup Language">XML</acronym></a>)
      </span></li></ul></li><li><span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><a href="http://archimedes.fas.harvard.edu/pollux/">Pollux</a> (direct
      access to dictionaries) </span></li></ul><h3><span style="font-size:
      x-small;">Other tools</span></h3><ul><li><span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><a href="http://archimedes.fas.harvard.edu/docs/ficus.html">ficus</a>
      (automatic insertion of page image and figure attributes for Archimedes documents)
      </span></li><li><span style="font-size: x-small;">Tools for the
      <acronym title="Cuneiform Digital Library
      Initiative">CDLI</acronym></span><ul><li><span style="font-size:
      x-small;">The <acronym title="ASCII Text Format">ATF</acronym> to <acronym
      title="XML Text Format">XTF</acronym> converter is now hosted at <a
      href="http://cdl.museum.upenn.edu/util/atfproc.html">UPenn</a></span></li><li><span
      style="font-size: x-small;"><a
      href="http://archimedes.fas.harvard.edu/cgi-bin/cdli/atf2www">atf2www
      converter</a></span></li></ul></li></ul><h3><span
      style="font-size: x-small;">For more
      information...</span></h3><blockquote> <span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><b><a
      href="http://www.news.harvard.edu/gazette/2003/11.13/01-archimedes.html">The Archimedes
      Project was featured in an article in the <i>Harvard University Gazette</i>
      (11-13-2003)</a>.</b></span><br /> <span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><a
      href="http://archimedes2.mpiwg-berlin.mpg.de/archimedes_templates/project.htm"><b>Read
      more about the project's goals, methods, and personnel.</b></a></span><br
      /> <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a
      href="http://archimedes.mpiwg-berlin.mpg.de/"><b>Visit the main Archimedes Project web
      site (at <acronym lang="de" title="Max-Planck-Institut für
      Wissenschaftsgeschichte">MPIWG</acronym>, Berlin).</b></a></span>
      </blockquote><h3><span style="font-size: x-small;">Research
      notes</span></h3><ul><li><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a
      href="http://archimedes.fas.harvard.edu/presentations/automatic.html">Automatic (Information
      Processing) Approaches to Document Content in the Archimedes
      Project</a></span></li><li><span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><a href="http://archimedes.fas.harvard.edu/docs/Arabic/">Support for Arabic
      Texts in the Archimedes Project</a></span></li><li><span
      style="font-size: x-small;"><a
      href="http://archimedes.fas.harvard.edu/docs/challenges/">The Challenge of the Humanities to
      the World Wide Web</a> (<a
      href="http://archimedes.fas.harvard.edu/docs/challenges.pdf"><img alt="PDF" border="0"
      height="16" src="http://archimedes.fas.harvard.edu/images/pdf.gif" width="16" /></a>)
      </span></li></ul><h3><span style="font-size: x-small;">Project
      documentation</span></h3><ul><li><span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><a href="http://archimedes.fas.harvard.edu/docs/repository/">Archimedes
      Project Repository: Working Draft 4</a> (<a
      href="http://archimedes.fas.harvard.edu/docs/repository.pdf"><img alt="PDF" border="0"
      height="16" src="http://archimedes.fas.harvard.edu/images/pdf.gif" width="16" /></a>)
      </span></li><li><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a
      href="http://archimedes.fas.harvard.edu/docs/catalog/">The Arboreal Catalog System</a>
      (<a href="http://archimedes.fas.harvard.edu/docs/catalog.pdf"><img alt="PDF"
      border="0" height="16" src="http://archimedes.fas.harvard.edu/images/pdf.gif" width="16"
      /></a>) </span></li><li><span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><a href="http://archimedes.fas.harvard.edu/docs/docspecs/">The Arboreal
      Docspecs System</a> (<a
      href="http://archimedes.fas.harvard.edu/docs/docspecs.pdf"><img alt="PDF" border="0"
      height="16" src="http://archimedes.fas.harvard.edu/images/pdf.gif" width="16" /></a>;
      <a href="http://archimedes.fas.harvard.edu/scrapbook/docspecs/">further
      resources</a>) </span></li><li><span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><a href="http://archimedes.fas.harvard.edu/docs/bundle/">Archimedes Bundle
      Structure</a> (<a href="http://archimedes.fas.harvard.edu/docs/bundle.pdf"><img
      alt="PDF" border="0" height="16" src="http://archimedes.fas.harvard.edu/images/pdf.gif"
      width="16" /></a>) </span></li><li><span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><a href="http://archimedes.fas.harvard.edu/docs/donatus-api/">The Donatus
      XML-RPC Interface (Donatus version 1.9)</a> (<a
      href="http://archimedes.fas.harvard.edu/docs/donatus-api.pdf"><img alt="PDF" border="0"
      height="16" src="http://archimedes.fas.harvard.edu/images/pdf.gif" width="16" /></a>)
      </span></li></ul></blockquote><div style="text-align:
      center;"></div>]]></content>
